Uses of Interface
xxl.core.collections.containers.Container

  • Packages that use Container 
    Package Description
    xxl.core.collections.bags
    Contains some bags.
    xxl.core.collections.containers
    Provides some containers.
    xxl.core.collections.containers.io
    Provides some containers that are able to store their blocks on disk.
    xxl.core.collections.containers.recordManager
    Provides a decorator container that is able to store records (of type Block ) which are of different size.
    xxl.core.collections.queues.io
    The package xxl.core.collections.queues.io provides some implementations of the queue datastructure using special containers (BlockBasedQueue), files (FileStackQueue) or streams (StreamQueue) for storing and receiving the data.
    xxl.core.indexStructures
    Provides important index structures like B-trees, R-trees, M-trees and bulk-loading-algorithms.
    xxl.core.indexStructures.builder
    Providing builder classes for various index structures.
    xxl.core.indexStructures.builder.BPlusTree
    The builder class for BPlusTrees.
    xxl.core.indexStructures.rtrees  
    xxl.core.indexStructures.vLengthBPlusTree
    Experimental Package for variable length B+tree implementation.
    xxl.core.io
    Provides classes and routines for system input and output through data streams, serialization, raw i/o and a FAT file system.
    xxl.core.spatial.histograms.utils  
    xxl.core.spatial.spatialBPlusTree  
    xxl.core.util.reflect
    This package contains useful utilities that need the reflection mechanisms of java sdk 1.3 or higher (dynamic proxies).

    • Uses of Container in xxl.core.collections.containers

      Classes in xxl.core.collections.containers that implement Container 
      Modifier and Type Class and Description
      class  AbstractContainer
      An AbstractContainer implements all methods of the Container interface except the central methods get, isUsed, ids, objectIdConverter, remove, reserve, size and update which are abstract.
      class  ArrayContainer
      Stores entries in ArrayList.
      class  ConstrainedDecoratorContainer
      The class provides a constained decorator for a container.
      class  CounterContainer
      This class decorates a container with a counter functionality and counts every call of an insert, get, update and remove method.
      class  DecoratorContainer
      The class provides a decorator for a container that follows the Decorator Design Pattern (for further details see Structural Patterns, Decorator in Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software by Erich Gamma, Richard Helm, Ralph Johnson, and John Vlissides).
      class  EmptyContainer
      This class provides an empty container.
      class  MapContainer
      This class provides an implementation of the Container interface that internally uses a map to store the (id,*)-elements.
      class  SynchronizedContainer
      The class provides a synchronized decorator for a container that follows the Decorator Design Pattern (for further details see Structural Patterns, Decorator in Design Patterns: Elements of Reusable Object-Oriented Software by Erich Gamma, Richard Helm, Ralph Johnson, and John Vlissides).
      class  UnmodifiableContainer
      This class provides a decorator for a given container that cannot be modified.
      class  VerificationContainer
      Verifies each write operation of a container, that means for example after an insert, the object is retrieved again with get and both objects are compared (using the equals method from Object).
